.Sh DESCRIPTION
After a long time of planning to do it and putting it off, I've finally
committed to a domain name, the relevant infrastructure, and an overall
direction for my personal website.
.Pp
I've noticed, talking about it to friends, a recurring pattern of mild to
moderate confusion about why I would want a personal blog in the first place. I
understand that it's fairly unusual broadly, and even in my particular social
spheres, but I do find it ironic.
.Pp
I'm trying my best to avoid sounding bitter about this - I'm really
.Em not
bitter about it - but I notice that, at least from my generation, there's no
surprise associated with, say, posting on mainstream social media. Creating and
maintaining an active Instagram account that documents your life, for example,
is considered completely normal amongst my generation. In fact, I've noticed
quite a bit of friction getting to know people, especially in dating, as a
result of not using Instagram in this way. My best guess is that the disparity
in surprise is down to the prevalent normalization of social media usage today,
and some assumptions about what a personal blog is all about.
.Pp
Either way, I don't blame people for being confused about it, but it does mean
I feel the need to keep justifying its existence in partial or full form, so I
figured it would probably be best to just write something down. So, these are
(most) of the reasons why this website exists.
