.It 
.Em I'm hoping it will help give me clarity on topics that I care about.
.Pp
I have a bit of a problem with over-explaining myself. If you're a friend of
mine, you're probably aware of this already. As I understand it, this happens
for a few reasons, but largely it is because my head can be very messy. I'm
not very skilled in expressing myself in verbal language on the fly, so my
spoken thoughts in conversation can be incoherent, sometimes irrelevant, and
hard to follow.  As a result, I'm often left feeling unsatisifed and
misunderstood after trying to explain something that means a lot to me. My
theory is that by posting some of these ramblings here, in written form, I can
better come to understand my own thoughts, which can help me to explain myself
succinctly and precisely when I need to. In this light, this website will be
something of a public journal, focused on the topics that mean a lot to me.
.It
.Em It's a kind of self-expression.
.Pp
I think all people desire self-expression; it might be the only reason that we
are here at all, at least in an individual capacity. It's clear that this is no
different today than it ever was. Things like Instagram, TikTok, and Twitter
are omnipresent in our lives, and it is not down to pure chance that it is this
way; these kinds of Apps provide people with entertainment, a sense of
connection, and a platform for self-expression. It's easy to forget that this
flowery ideal is
.Em kind of the entire point
in a world constructed, brick by brick, by hidden forces, to keep us busy,
judging ourselves predominantly by our economic contribution and the quality of
our pointless possessions.
.Pp
Bitter cynacism aside, I've been feeling, day by day, more and more discontent
with the lack of self-expression in my life. I think that this is not a rare
feeling to have, though it might be rare to understand it; it seems that the
entire concept of a stereotypical man is one of quiet resignation from
expression of any kind.
.Pp
This website is my attempt at stepping into the limelight for a change. It's
not that I think that I am particularly important, clever or interesting - far
from it, though I'm quite sure some readers will choose to interpret the
writing of this site with an aura of self-importance regardless of what I
claim. But I think all people are owed the freedom to express themselves, be
heard and seen, and I've taken to allow myself that freedom as well.
.Pp
I know that this entire segment is, through and through, a testament of my
privileged life. I don't deny that it is a privilege to have the time to even
think about any of this, while some are wondering where their next meal will
be, or whether it will be their house that is striked next. I think, again, I
will be judged for this relentlessly by some no matter what I do. But it is my
philosophy that you must care for yourself before you can care for others.
This is me caring for myself, so that I may better help others.
